[WATER SPLASHES]

02:16.386 --> 02:18.889
Nice going, Charlie Brown.

02:19.056 --> 02:22.392
I took that rock 4,000 years
to get to shore,

02:22.559 --> 02:25.520
and now you've thrown it back.

02:25.687 --> 02:28.774
Everything I do makes me feel guilty.

04:41.239 --> 04:43.450
[BOTH LAUGHING]

04:48.205 --> 04:51.625
You know, kid.
You and I make a great pair.

05:11.937 --> 05:15.899
It‘s nice to lie in the sun
and just do nothing.

05:17.734 --> 05:22.072
Of course, it's better
if you're with someone you like.

05:22.239 --> 05:25.242
You kind of like me,
don‘t you, Snoopy?

05:28.453 --> 05:31.039
Why don‘t we meet here again
tomorrow?

05:31.665 --> 05:34.584
If you‘ll come,
I'll bring a picnic lunch.

05:34.751 --> 05:38.255
We'll have sandwiches, cookies
and lemonade and potato chips

05:38.421 --> 05:40.590
and everything, okay?

05:40.757 --> 05:42.592
And we‘ll build another sand castle.

05:42.759 --> 05:45.595
Only this time,
we'll build an even bigger one.

05:45.762 --> 05:48.765
We'll have a great time.
Will you come?

05:49.766 --> 05:52.310
Good. I'll see you tomorrow.

05:55.772 --> 05:57.774
[DICE RATTLING]

05:59.359 --> 06:01.653
I wonder where Snoopy is.

06:03.780 --> 06:06.616
I've got Boardwalk and Park Place.

06:06.783 --> 06:09.744
I'm going to destroy you economically,
Charlie Brown.

06:10.453 --> 06:11.955
I'll never give up.

06:12.122 --> 06:15.542
I have a philosophy that tells me,
no matter how bad things get,

06:15.709 --> 06:18.503
they will always turn out good
in the end.

06:19.212 --> 06:22.507
That's not a philosophy,
that's stupidity.

06:25.010 --> 06:26.761
CHARLIE:
Seven.

06:27.762 --> 06:29.431
Go directly to jail.

06:29.598 --> 06:30.891
Do not pass go.

06:31.057 --> 06:32.976
Do not collect $200.

06:33.143 --> 06:35.312
Good grief.

06:35.478 --> 06:37.647
When you get out of jail,
Charlie Brown,

06:37.814 --> 06:40.483
you‘re gonna land on my Boardwalk
or Park Place,

06:40.650 --> 06:43.320
and then you'll be destroyed.

06:44.571 --> 06:49.326
Ha! Twelve, doubles.
That means I get another turn.

06:50.327 --> 06:54.331
Oh, no, not on Pacific!
With hotels!

06:55.332 --> 06:58.501
Pay me $1,275, please.

06:58.668 --> 07:02.631
Schroeder. Schroeder.
How about a beep on the nose?

07:02.797 --> 07:06.176
- A what?
- Beep.

07:06.343 --> 07:09.346
A beep on the nose is a sign
of great affection.

07:09.512 --> 07:13.016
I'd rather have the $1,275, please.

07:13.183 --> 07:17.687
- Pay up.
- But I haven't got $1,275.

07:17.854 --> 07:21.524
If you can't pay up,
then I guess you're bankrupt.

07:21.691 --> 07:24.235
LUCY: I am not bankrupt.
- It's almost dark.

07:24.402 --> 07:26.571
Snoopy isn‘t home yet.

07:27.197 --> 07:30.033
I wonder where that dog is.

07:30.742 --> 07:32.077
There he is.

07:32.243 --> 07:34.496
I wonder where he‘s been all day.

07:34.663 --> 07:36.539
What an independent dog.

07:36.706 --> 07:39.042
He comes and goes as he pleases.

07:39.209 --> 07:42.253
But I have to stay home
and fix his supper.

07:48.218 --> 07:51.846
Ow! Ow! Ow.

07:52.013 --> 07:53.473
Rats!

07:55.266 --> 07:59.229
All right, it's supper time.
Come and get your supper.

07:59.938 --> 08:02.023
Do you see this finger?

08:02.190 --> 08:06.653
I cut it opening a stupid can
of dog food for your stupid supper.

08:06.820 --> 08:08.697
I hope you appreciate it.

08:08.863 --> 08:13.034
Besides that, it wasn't a finger,
it was my thumb.

08:17.247 --> 08:20.041
You've been acting
awfully independent lately.

08:20.208 --> 08:23.253
Don't forget that I'm the one
who feeds you.

08:23.420 --> 08:26.381
I'm the one who takes care of you.

08:26.840 --> 08:29.551
Look at me when I'm talking to you.

08:29.718 --> 08:31.970
Without me, you'd be nothing.

08:32.136 --> 08:35.265
Everything you have,
you have because of me.

08:35.432 --> 08:37.433
Even that collar around your neck.

08:37.600 --> 08:39.184
Why, I remember the day I went out

08:39.352 --> 08:41.855
and bought that collar
with money I had worked for

08:42.022 --> 08:44.524
and had saved and...

08:50.405 --> 08:52.574
I hate it when he does that.

08:52.741 --> 08:54.743
[SEAGULLS CAWING]

09:05.920 --> 09:08.548
[WHISTLING]

09:48.546 --> 09:51.174
[SIREN WAILING
AND WHISTLE BLOWING]

10:09.192 --> 10:11.402
[GIBBERING]

10:19.911 --> 10:22.122
I think I've been stood up.

10:37.220 --> 10:39.430
[GIBBERING]

10:41.516 --> 10:43.143
[SIGHS]

10:44.352 --> 10:46.354
[GIBBERING]

12:00.929 --> 12:02.096
[THUDDING]

12:34.128 --> 12:36.965
Maybe I came on too strong for him.

12:44.681 --> 12:47.767
I know why you want me
to go to the library!

12:47.934 --> 12:51.271
You‘re trying to trick me
into learning how to read.

12:51.437 --> 12:55.692
That's what you're trying to do.
Who cares about reading?

12:55.858 --> 12:57.277
The next thing you know,

12:57.443 --> 13:02.282
you‘ll want me to conjugate all
those verbs and split those infinitives.

13:02.448 --> 13:04.242
I hate reading.

13:04.784 --> 13:07.287
I just want to be a good housewife.

13:07.453 --> 13:12.250
Shh! You have to be real quiet in here.
Now, come on.

13:30.393 --> 13:31.811
[GROANS]

13:59.464 --> 14:01.299
[GIGGLES]

14:17.398 --> 14:19.859
[LAUGHING]

14:39.796 --> 14:41.464
[GIBBERING]

15:05.279 --> 15:08.366
[SHRIEKS]

15:49.449 --> 15:51.451
[GROANING]

15:56.789 --> 15:58.791
[YELLING]

16:15.558 --> 16:17.560
[SCREAMING]

16:30.031 --> 16:31.908
LINUS:
Oh, Snoopy.

17:10.695 --> 17:12.198
[GRUNTS]

17:16.327 --> 17:17.744
[GRUNTING]

17:50.278 --> 17:52.280
[PANTING]

