I need a fundamental pal</i>

30:42.758 --> 30:45.260
<i>I’ll depend on you
You’ll depend on me</i>

30:45.427 --> 30:47.095
<i>Speaking psychologically</i>

30:47.262 --> 30:50.474
<i>We’ll both have fundamental
Friend dependability</i>

30:50.640 --> 30:53.185
<i>Fundamental friend dependability</i>

30:53.352 --> 30:55.812
<i>I’ll have fun with you
You’ll have fun with me</i>

30:55.979 --> 30:59.274
<i>That’s fundamental
Friend dependability</i>

30:59.441 --> 31:02.027
Here, Rex. Here, Rex. Here.

31:04.529 --> 31:07.282
- Heel, Rex. Heel.
SNOOPY: Aah!

31:07.449 --> 31:09.409
Heel, Rex. Heel.

31:09.576 --> 31:11.578
[SNOOPY GRUNTING]

31:17.459 --> 31:21.046
First thing to do with you, Rex,
is to bathe you.

31:21.213 --> 31:22.923
I hope you like baths

31:23.090 --> 31:25.300
because my doggy has
to be real clean.

31:25.467 --> 31:27.094
Okay, Rex?

31:27.594 --> 31:30.013
Okay, in you go, Rex.

31:32.516 --> 31:37.854
<i>Speaking hygienically
We’ve got to wash away each ﬂea</i>

31:38.021 --> 31:40.482
<i>Rub a-dub a-dub
I’II scrub you in the tub</i>

31:40.649 --> 31:42.609
<i>Oh, how squeaky clean you’ll be</i>

31:42.776 --> 31:47.030
<i>Because of fundamental
Friend dependability</i>

31:47.197 --> 31:49.783
<i>I will disinfect your whole anatomy</i>

31:49.950 --> 31:52.369
<i>When you’ve got a chum
Who scrubs you till you’re numb</i>

31:52.536 --> 31:55.872
<i>That’s fundamental
Friend dependability</i>

31:56.039 --> 31:57.666
Down, Rex!

31:57.833 --> 31:59.209
Heel, Rex. Heel!

32:00.585 --> 32:03.088
Rex! Rex! You naughty dog.

32:03.255 --> 32:05.715
Rex! Down, boy, bad dog!

32:05.882 --> 32:08.093
Heel, Rex. Heel.

32:10.178 --> 32:12.472
I'm glad you like baths.

32:18.687 --> 32:21.731
I want you to be real clean
so we can play dress-up.

32:25.444 --> 32:28.113
Down, Rex. Down, boy.

32:28.280 --> 32:30.615
Stay, Rex, stay.

32:30.782 --> 32:34.161
I'm gonna close the door
so you won't run away.

32:34.327 --> 32:36.580
Then we'll play dolls, okay?

32:37.664 --> 32:40.667
[WOODSTOCK GIBBERS
AND SNOOPY SIGHS]

32:41.793 --> 32:45.088
I always wanted a Sheepdog.
You stick with me, Rex.

32:45.255 --> 32:50.469
<i>Every little shaggy pup
Ought to get to gussie up</i>

32:50.635 --> 32:54.639
<i>I will pour the tea
Just for you and me</i>

32:54.806 --> 32:59.102
<i>Oh, how proper we will be</i>

32:59.269 --> 33:02.939
<i>’Cause we got fundamental
Friend dependability</i>

33:03.106 --> 33:05.650
<i>Fundamental friend dependability</i>

33:05.817 --> 33:08.320
<i>Fundamental friend dependa
Fundamental friend dependa</i>

33:08.487 --> 33:10.947
<i>Fundamental friend dependability</i>

33:13.074 --> 33:15.494
You naughty dog.
You got your dress dirty.

33:15.660 --> 33:17.329
I'll have to spank you.

33:18.121 --> 33:20.123
[YELPING]

33:20.832 --> 33:24.377
Down, boy, down!
Here, Rex! Down, Rex!

33:24.544 --> 33:27.464
Bad dog. Bad dog!
Come back, Rex!

33:27.631 --> 33:29.174
Here, boy.

33:41.102 --> 33:44.356
You naughty dog.
Raising all this commotion.

33:44.523 --> 33:46.691
Mom says, if I'm gonna keep you,

33:46.858 --> 33:49.736
I gotta take you
to the vet for a checkup.

33:49.903 --> 33:52.405
You probably need
about a dozen shots.

33:52.572 --> 33:53.823
[GRUNTING]

33:55.492 --> 33:58.870
I'II walk you to the vet's,
that will be great, hey, Rex?

33:59.037 --> 34:00.830
Heel, Rex, heel.

34:05.001 --> 34:06.878
I'm so glad I found you.

34:07.045 --> 34:11.257
Mom always said we needed a dog
to get rid of our table scraps.

34:20.809 --> 34:22.811
[DOGS BARKING]

34:31.902 --> 34:33.362
[BOTH GIGGLE]

34:47.252 --> 34:50.130
Here, Rex. Here, Rex. Here.

34:51.005 --> 34:52.591
[PANTING]

34:52.757 --> 34:55.302
[DOOR OPENS, THEN CLOSES]

34:58.513 --> 35:01.266
Rex! You naughty dog, Rex!

36:05.080 --> 36:06.706
[PANTING]

36:11.753 --> 36:13.004
[SNOOPY SHRIEKS]

36:30.814 --> 36:32.273
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

36:57.924 --> 36:59.634
I'm depressed, Linus.

36:59.801 --> 37:02.887
I need an encouraging word
to cheer me up.

37:03.763 --> 37:06.850
Happiness lies in our destiny,
like a cloud in the sky

37:07.016 --> 37:08.977
before the storms of tomorrow destroy

37:09.144 --> 37:11.604
the dreams of yesterday
and last week.

37:12.480 --> 37:15.900
I think that blanket is
doing something to you.

38:20.381 --> 38:21.424
[THUDDING]

39:12.517 --> 39:14.102
[SIGHS]

39:19.524 --> 39:20.817
[WHISTLING]

40:31.471 --> 40:33.473
[BOTH LAUGHING]

40:50.615 --> 40:52.617
[YAWNS]

40:55.578 --> 40:57.455
[GIBBERING]

41:45.086 --> 41:46.879
[CRANKING]

41:47.046 --> 41:49.048
[CLOCK TICKING]

41:55.471 --> 41:57.473
[ALARM RINGS]

41:57.640 --> 41:59.642
[LAUGHING]

42:08.192 --> 42:10.611
There's only one thing to be done,
Charlie Brown.

42:11.654 --> 42:15.074
I think you should disown
that ungrateful dog.

42:15.241 --> 42:16.534
Disown him?

42:16.701 --> 42:18.369
You have to face it, Charlie Brown,

42:18.536 --> 42:21.622
nobody made him leave,
he went because he wanted to.

42:22.415 --> 42:24.167
You'll just have to get another dog.

42:24.333 --> 42:26.419
I don‘t want another dog.

42:26.961 --> 42:33.134
And I still say, if I don‘t find out
who Lila is, I'll go crazy!

42:34.802 --> 42:36.929
He's hopeless.

42:40.183 --> 42:42.727
Listen to that music, Chuck,
it's a carnival.

42:42.894 --> 42:45.646
Doesn't that do something to you?
Listen.

42:46.939 --> 42:48.649
It's a beautiful evening, Chuck.

42:48.816 --> 42:51.652
The air is warm.
The sky is filled with stars.

42:51.819 --> 42:54.197
And I've got a whole pocketful
of tickets for the carnival.

42:54.363 --> 42:56.365
Come on, let's go.

42:59.827 --> 43:04.123
Listen, people are laughing, Chuck.
They're having a good time.

43:05.958 --> 43:08.544
You can‘t let yourself get
into a mood like this.

43:08.711 --> 43:11.255
I know you miss Snoopy.
I miss him too.

43:11.422 --> 43:15.259
But if you let yourself get into a mood,
no one will want to be around you.

43:15.426 --> 43:18.513
No one likes a moody person, Chuck.
Take it from me.

43:18.679 --> 43:19.889
I learned a long time ago

43:20.056 --> 43:23.309
that if you go around in a mood
feeling sorry for yourself,

43:23.476 --> 43:24.811
you do it alone.

43:24.977 --> 43:27.021
And I mean alone, Chuck.

43:35.822 --> 43:36.864
[GRUNTS]

43:37.031 --> 43:38.157
I don‘t know.

43:38.324 --> 43:40.409
I've seen people get sick
on merry-go-rounds

43:40.576 --> 43:42.453
and Ferris wheels
and roller coasters,

43:42.620 --> 43:44.831
but you‘re the first person
I've ever seen who got sick

43:44.997 --> 43:46.999
going through the turnstile.

43:48.584 --> 43:52.171
Hey, look at that, Chuck.
Come on, let's go!

44:02.765 --> 44:04.392
[CHARLIE GRUNTING]

44:10.356 --> 44:12.817
We‘re having a good time,
aren't we, Chuck?

44:13.401 --> 44:16.112
I love this kind of life. I like action.

44:16.279 --> 44:17.905
I'm a moving-type person.

44:18.072 --> 44:20.616
When nothing is moving,
I feel low.

44:20.783 --> 44:23.369
That's why I always keep moving.

44:58.529 --> 45:01.616
Does your kind ever think
about love, Chuck?

45:01.782 --> 45:05.453
- What do you mean, my kind?
- I'm sorry.

45:05.620 --> 45:08.331
I didn‘t mean to put it that way.
No offense.

45:08.497 --> 45:10.875
I apologize. Friends?

45:12.668 --> 45:14.837
You touched my hand, Chuck.

45:16.839 --> 45:19.884
Hey, look here,
a fortune-telling machine.

45:20.051 --> 45:21.844
Let‘s get our fortune told, Chuck.

45:22.011 --> 45:25.181
Maybe we can find out something
about ourselves.

45:28.434 --> 45:32.772
PEPPERMINT PATTY [READING]:

45:36.901 --> 45:38.527
CHARLIE [READING]:

45:42.448 --> 45:45.660
You kind of like being with me,
don't you, Chuck?

45:48.579 --> 45:51.332
What do you think love is, Chuck?

45:52.166 --> 45:57.838
Well, years ago, my dad owned
a black 1934 two-door sedan.

45:58.005 --> 46:02.093
- What's that got to do with love?
- Well, this is what he told me.

46:02.260 --> 46:04.595
There was this real cute girl, see?

46:04.762 --> 46:06.931
She used to go for rides
with him in his car,

46:07.098 --> 46:08.516
and whenever he'd call for her,

46:08.683 --> 46:10.559
he would always hold open
the car door for her.

46:10.726 --> 46:13.354
After she got in
and he had closed the door,

46:13.521 --> 46:16.315
he'd walk around the back
of the car, to the driver's side.

46:16.482 --> 46:18.067
But before he could get there,

46:18.234 --> 46:21.320
she would reach over and press
the button, locking him out.

46:22.196 --> 46:26.742
Then, she'd just sit there
and wrinkle her nose and grin at him.

46:27.451 --> 46:29.161
That's what I think love is.

46:31.580 --> 46:35.167
Sometimes
I wonder about you, Chuck.

46:45.636 --> 46:47.638
[BELL RINGING]

47:36.771 --> 47:38.022
[HICCUPS]

47:40.274 --> 47:42.276
[GIBBERING]

47:53.746 --> 47:55.748
[GIBBERING]

47:57.208 --> 47:59.210
[LAUGHING]

48:17.478 --> 48:19.480
[LAUGHING]

