[YAWNS]

50:52.967 --> 50:54.969
[SIRENS WAILING]

51:07.690 --> 51:08.732
[GROANS]

51:58.532 --> 51:59.950
[BUTTON BUZZES]

52:18.385 --> 52:19.803
[BUTTON BUZZES]

52:57.383 --> 52:58.676
Snoopy!

53:00.386 --> 53:02.388
I knew you'd come.

53:06.016 --> 53:07.267
[SIGHS]

53:10.270 --> 53:12.690
Hi, Chuck. Any news from old Snoop?

53:12.856 --> 53:15.150
No. No news.

53:15.984 --> 53:18.862
He's never been gone
this long before.

53:46.098 --> 53:49.977
You've got to agree,
he's gone because of me.

53:50.144 --> 53:53.188
Maybe I came on too strong for him.

53:56.275 --> 54:00.028
Right after our fight,
he kissed me and I fainted.

54:00.195 --> 54:04.658
I think, he thinks, I think
there's something wrong with him.

54:28.640 --> 54:32.394
He wanted my blanket,
I wouldn‘t let go.

54:32.561 --> 54:36.523
He left because I was hostile
and unkind to him.

54:39.526 --> 54:43.405
I made him feel unwanted,
like he was a pest.

54:43.572 --> 54:47.117
Now I'm going out of my mind for him.

55:15.187 --> 55:17.773
- Do you think pets are important?
- Sure.

55:17.940 --> 55:21.151
A friend of mine at school got
some goldfish for his birthday.

55:21.318 --> 55:24.404
- I don't think he really wanted them.
-Hmm.

55:24.571 --> 55:27.866
How did you happen to get Snoopy,
Charlie Brown?

55:28.033 --> 55:30.953
Well, I'm not quite sure
because I was kind of young.

55:31.119 --> 55:34.665
I think it started because of something
that happened at a playground.

55:34.832 --> 55:37.876
I was playing in the sandbox
with a couple of other kids.

55:38.043 --> 55:39.962
I can‘t even remember
who they were.

55:40.629 --> 55:42.548
Anyway, all of a sudden,

55:42.714 --> 55:45.843
one of them poured a whole bucket
of sand over my head.

55:46.009 --> 55:48.345
I started crying... I guess.

55:48.512 --> 55:50.639
And my mother came running up
and took me home.

55:52.808 --> 55:55.185
It's kind of embarrassing now
to talk about it.

55:55.352 --> 55:59.022
Anyway, the next day we drove out
to the Daisy Hill Puppy Farm,

55:59.189 --> 56:01.900
and my mother and dad
bought me a dog.

56:02.067 --> 56:05.112
People buy pets
for strange reasons.

56:07.447 --> 56:08.824
[SIGHS]

56:10.409 --> 56:13.412
I just don't know what to do, Linus.

56:14.037 --> 56:16.415
If I don't find out
what happened to Snoopy,

56:16.582 --> 56:18.834
I think I'll go out of my mind.

56:19.001 --> 56:21.211
If you‘ll calm down for a minute,
Charlie Brown,

56:21.378 --> 56:26.008
I may be able to conduct
a little private investigation.

56:26.174 --> 56:30.387
Just what I need,
a blanket-carrying Sherlock Holmes.

56:30.554 --> 56:34.391
I wonder if it would help to call
the Daisy Hill Puppy Farm.

56:34.558 --> 56:37.686
They might know something
about him that we don‘t know.

56:40.063 --> 56:42.065
I don't understand it.

56:42.232 --> 56:44.651
Every morning I brought him
a toasted English muffin

56:44.818 --> 56:46.612
with grape jelly on it.

56:46.778 --> 56:50.240
Sometimes at noon,
I'd even fix him a nice salad.

56:51.658 --> 56:53.994
He wrote all those letters
to the editor.

56:54.161 --> 56:56.413
Why doesn't he write me a letter?

56:57.998 --> 57:01.543
Snoopy, come home!

57:02.502 --> 57:05.130
I'm feeling so much better
now that you‘re here.

57:05.297 --> 57:07.215
I hope I can go home soon.

57:09.801 --> 57:10.886
[DOOR OPENS]

57:12.679 --> 57:15.015
Thank you, nurse. Thank you.

57:18.268 --> 57:20.479
[DOOR CLOSES
AND SNOOPY SIGHS]

57:25.150 --> 57:29.863
I'm feeling better every day.
Perhaps soon, we can go home.

57:30.948 --> 57:32.240
[SNOOPY GULPS]

57:32.407 --> 57:35.327
I know that when my mother sees
how you‘ve made me well,

57:35.494 --> 57:37.079
she'll let me take you home with me.

57:37.245 --> 57:39.831
I'll keep you with me forever.

57:39.998 --> 57:42.167
What's the matter, Snoopy?

57:42.334 --> 57:44.753
You do want to go home with me,
don't you?

57:44.920 --> 57:46.922
[SOBBING]

57:48.215 --> 57:51.969
You poor dear.
You're homesick, aren't you?

57:52.135 --> 57:54.471
But we'll be good for each other.

57:55.639 --> 57:59.476
Hello? Hello, Humane Society?

57:59.643 --> 58:02.479
I'm calling about this lost dog,
you see.

58:04.189 --> 58:05.732
Describe him?

58:05.899 --> 58:09.194
I don't know how to describe him.
He's just a stupid beagle!

58:10.362 --> 58:11.613
I've had it!

58:11.780 --> 58:15.993
Let old wishy-washy Charlie Brown
find his dog himself.

58:27.629 --> 58:30.424
Hello, Daisy Hill Puppy Farm?

58:30.590 --> 58:34.011
I'm calling in regard
to a dog named Snoopy.

58:35.721 --> 58:37.222
Uh-huh.

58:38.223 --> 58:40.642
That's right. Charlie Brown.

58:41.226 --> 58:43.437
Uh-huh. Oh.

58:43.603 --> 58:45.147
Really?

58:46.606 --> 58:49.026
Wow. I'll bet he never knew that.

58:49.192 --> 58:50.652
That explains a lot of things.

58:54.948 --> 58:58.118
[PANTING]
Charlie Brown! Charlie Brown!

58:58.285 --> 59:00.037
Charlie Brown!

59:01.997 --> 59:04.207
I have news about Snoopy.

59:04.374 --> 59:07.210
All right, tell me, what happened?

59:07.377 --> 59:10.922
If you don‘t tell me what happened
to Snoopy, I'll go crazy.

59:11.089 --> 59:13.717
The first thing I did
in my investigation

59:13.884 --> 59:16.803
was to call
the Daisy Hill Puppy Farm.

59:16.970 --> 59:20.015
I found out something
that will amaze you.

59:20.932 --> 59:23.685
In fact, I hesitate to tell you.

59:24.853 --> 59:29.858
Are you ready for a shock?
He wasn't ready for a shock.

59:33.862 --> 59:36.448
How can I tell you something
that will shock you

59:36.615 --> 59:38.617
if you pass out
before I can tell you?

59:38.784 --> 59:39.868
I'm sorry.

59:40.035 --> 59:42.496
I've been hyperventilating
a lot lately.

59:42.662 --> 59:44.164
Well, anyway.

59:44.331 --> 59:48.043
Here's what I found out when I called
the Daisy Hill Puppy Farm.

59:50.212 --> 59:52.964
You are not Snoopy's original owner.

59:55.300 --> 59:56.927
Oh, good grief.

59:58.220 --> 01:00:02.015
You bought Snoopy
in the month of October, right?

01:00:02.182 --> 01:00:05.060
According to the records
at the Daisy Hill Puppy Farm,

01:00:05.227 --> 01:00:08.688
Snoopy was bought
by another family in August.

01:00:08.855 --> 01:00:11.525
This family had
a little girl named Lila.

01:00:11.691 --> 01:00:14.528
Snoopy and Lila loved
each other very much,

01:00:14.694 --> 01:00:17.280
but they had to move
and the family decided

01:00:17.447 --> 01:00:19.991
they just couldn't keep Snoopy.
So they returned him.

01:00:23.912 --> 01:00:26.498
You got a used dog, Charlie Brown.

01:00:33.296 --> 01:00:36.800
- So that's why Snoopy left.
- Sure.

01:00:36.967 --> 01:00:39.719
He had tried to forget her
all these years.

01:00:39.886 --> 01:00:43.306
But when he found out she was
in the hospital, he ran off to see her.

01:00:48.562 --> 01:00:52.732
I‘ll bet he wishes
he was still her dog instead of mine.

01:01:09.124 --> 01:01:11.293
- That's funny.
WOODSTOCK: Hee-hee.

01:01:12.210 --> 01:01:14.838
Well, Snoopy,
this is our last day together.

01:01:15.630 --> 01:01:16.798
What are we going to do?

01:01:18.008 --> 01:01:21.052
You're coming to visit me saved me.

01:01:23.972 --> 01:01:26.933
Are you sure you don‘t want
to come home with me?

01:01:28.643 --> 01:01:30.478
It's up to you, Snoopy.

01:01:30.645 --> 01:01:33.064
You can go to your other owner
if you want to,

01:01:33.231 --> 01:01:35.734
but I wish
you'd come home with me.

01:02:05.847 --> 01:02:07.307
[SOBS]

01:02:15.398 --> 01:02:17.025
Snoopy.

01:02:17.192 --> 01:02:20.362
Oh, I'm so glad you came back.

01:02:20.528 --> 01:02:23.907
This means you want to come
and live with me, doesn't it?

01:02:25.575 --> 01:02:29.287
Why don't you go back home.
Maybe you could settle your affairs.

01:02:29.454 --> 01:02:31.957
You could say goodbye
to all of your old friends,

01:02:32.123 --> 01:02:34.584
then you could come
and meet me at my house.

01:02:34.751 --> 01:02:36.962
Now, promise me
you'll hurry back.

01:02:37.128 --> 01:02:41.091
After this, you'll never leave again.
Promise me.

01:02:45.887 --> 01:02:47.806
Hurry back, honey.

01:03:00.568 --> 01:03:02.570
[TYPEWRITER CLICKING]

01:03:12.622 --> 01:03:14.499
Hey, you‘re back.

01:03:14.666 --> 01:03:16.918
I heard about Lila.
Did you see her?

01:03:17.085 --> 01:03:18.211
Was she well?

01:03:18.378 --> 01:03:20.171
Where did you stay
all the time you were gone?

01:03:20.338 --> 01:03:22.674
Was Lila nice to you?
Why didn't you write?

01:03:22.841 --> 01:03:26.845
Are you hungry? Are you well?
Can I do anything for you?

01:03:29.764 --> 01:03:32.267
I'm not getting any answers.

01:03:34.352 --> 01:03:36.688
I can't stand it!

01:03:48.533 --> 01:03:50.201
What's this?

01:03:50.952 --> 01:03:53.496
"I, Snoopy, being of sound mind,

01:03:53.663 --> 01:03:57.500
do bequeath to Charlie Brown,
my previous owner--"

01:03:57.667 --> 01:03:59.377
Previous owner?

01:04:01.421 --> 01:04:03.340
"--my best wishes for the future.

01:04:03.506 --> 01:04:07.177
My treasured belongings will be given
to my friends as follows."

01:04:07.344 --> 01:04:10.513
What's going on here?
Why do you mean by all this?

01:04:12.182 --> 01:04:17.062
"My croquet set I leave to Linus,
as well as the chess set.

01:04:17.228 --> 01:04:18.605
My record collection

01:04:18.772 --> 01:04:20.899
I place in the capable hands
of Schroeder.

01:04:21.066 --> 01:04:25.445
Carpeting and rest of the furnishings
to my favorite charity,

01:04:25.612 --> 01:04:27.864
the American Humane Association.

01:04:28.031 --> 01:04:30.450
Thus, with the settling of my affair,

01:04:30.617 --> 01:04:33.203
I return to Lila who needs me."

01:04:36.414 --> 01:04:38.416
[PLAYING JAUNTY TUN E]

01:04:42.462 --> 01:04:45.465
We are gathered together
at this farewell party

01:04:45.632 --> 01:04:49.719
to pay tribute and say goodbye
to a very close friend.

01:04:51.304 --> 01:04:55.308
Perhaps I could persuade
some of you to say a few words.

01:04:55.475 --> 01:04:56.935
Lucy?

01:05:01.523 --> 01:05:03.900
With a heavy heart
I stand before you

01:05:04.067 --> 01:05:10.365
as we all gather to say
our last goodbyes to Snoopy.

01:05:10.532 --> 01:05:13.159
He leaves us
in the prime of his life.

01:05:13.326 --> 01:05:14.577
[SOBBING]

01:05:14.744 --> 01:05:18.206
He wasn't much of a dog,
but who is?

01:05:18.373 --> 01:05:20.542
We shall miss our furry friend.

01:05:20.708 --> 01:05:25.630
So at this time I want to offer
this gesture of friendship.

01:05:30.218 --> 01:05:32.470
A little gift for old times' sake.

01:05:32.637 --> 01:05:33.680
[SOBS]

01:05:33.847 --> 01:05:35.890
Farewell, Snoopy.

01:05:42.439 --> 01:05:45.608
Next, I would like to call on Schroeder.

01:05:49.779 --> 01:05:54.367
Well, first I would like to thank
Snoopy for the record albums.

01:05:54.534 --> 01:05:57.954
And for the many great times
we have had together.

01:05:58.121 --> 01:05:59.581
[SOBBING]

01:05:59.747 --> 01:06:04.002
Here, Snoopy, a little token
of my friendship.

01:06:10.925 --> 01:06:16.931
And now a word from Snoopy's
ex-owner, Charlie Brown.

01:06:21.394 --> 01:06:22.437
[GULPS]

01:06:28.860 --> 01:06:30.445
[WAILING]

01:06:31.070 --> 01:06:33.281
[WAILS]

01:06:40.038 --> 01:06:44.834
Snoopy, with a heavy heart
and all the best wishes...

01:06:46.503 --> 01:06:48.379
...this present.

01:06:49.547 --> 01:06:51.382
Goodbye, Snoopy.

01:06:55.011 --> 01:06:56.971
I'm sorry to see you go, Snoopy.

01:06:57.138 --> 01:06:59.849
I'm sorry we never caught any rabbits.

01:07:02.268 --> 01:07:03.728
[SOBS]

01:07:07.982 --> 01:07:09.400
[COUGHING]

01:07:15.240 --> 01:07:17.242
[SOBBING]

01:07:42.308 --> 01:07:44.310
[SMOOCHING]

01:07:45.728 --> 01:07:47.146
Beep.

01:08:09.460 --> 01:08:11.462
[PLAYING JAUNTY TUN E]

01:08:14.924 --> 01:08:16.926
[ALL SOBBING]

01:08:50.167 --> 01:08:52.170
[GIBBERING]

01:11:16.147 --> 01:11:17.815
[SIGHS]

01:11:22.737 --> 01:11:26.115
CHARLIE: <i>Why can’t we get
all the people together in the world…</i>

01:11:26.282 --> 01:11:28.159
<i>that we really like,</i>

01:11:29.619 --> 01:11:32.288
<i>and then just stay together forever?</i>

01:11:34.665 --> 01:11:36.542
<i>Someone would leave.</i>

01:11:37.460 --> 01:11:39.420
<i>Someone always leaves.</i>

01:11:41.839 --> 01:11:44.342
<i>And then we’d have to say goodbye.</i>

01:11:47.178 --> 01:11:49.514
<i>I hate goodbyes.</i>

01:11:55.895 --> 01:11:57.313
[SIGHS]

01:12:33.432 --> 01:12:37.895
<i>You know what I need?
I need more hellos.</i>

01:13:33.451 --> 01:13:35.036
[DOORBELL BUZZES]

01:13:52.094 --> 01:13:57.224
Snoopy, you finally got here.
We‘ve been expecting you.

01:13:57.391 --> 01:14:00.603
Our whole family is eager
to see you again.

01:14:00.770 --> 01:14:04.440
And I can hardly wait
to have you meet my cat.

01:14:04.607 --> 01:14:08.778
You'll just love each other.
He's the sweetest thing.

01:14:32.134 --> 01:14:33.594
I must be cracking up.

01:14:33.761 --> 01:14:37.640
I can't sleep, and today
I even opened a can of dog food

01:14:37.807 --> 01:14:41.644
and took it out to the doghouse
before I remembered he was gone.

01:14:41.811 --> 01:14:46.107
I guess we all miss Snoopy.
I hope he's happy with Lila.

01:14:49.610 --> 01:14:51.278
[BOTH SIGH]

01:14:51.445 --> 01:14:54.532
Have you ever thought of getting
another dog, Charlie Brown?

01:14:54.699 --> 01:14:56.993
No, never again.

01:14:57.159 --> 01:15:00.413
I don‘t ever want to go through
such an ordeal again.

01:15:11.507 --> 01:15:13.509
[WHISTLING]

01:15:55.885 --> 01:15:57.887
[WHISTLING]

01:16:02.391 --> 01:16:03.434
[THUDDING]

01:16:07.271 --> 01:16:09.065
[GIBBERING]

01:16:14.570 --> 01:16:16.572
[WHISTLING]

